    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Symptoms generally start within one hour of ingestion, and usually resolves within 12 hours (if untreated)\nFlushing, warmth, erythematous and urticarial\nrash\n,\npalpitations\n,\ndizziness\n,\ndiarrhea\n, perioral burning,\nitching\n, or edema\nMay also see severe throbbing\nheadache\n,\nblurred vision\n,\ntachycardia\n, and\nrespiratory distress",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
